// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - OpenTheSafe 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1269202660" "<color orange>This is either the smartest or the dumbest safe you've ever seen.  Either way, you have the keycode that will 'unlock' the safe.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3813256124" "Enter the safe keycode"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1156573975" "<color orange>Once you enter the code, you hear a racket coming out of the case of the computer.  A rank-smelling stream of smoke begins billowing out from the air vents from case.  A second later, a panel opens on the side and a large bundle of bills are revealed.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3026394022" "Grab the cash!"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1798564250" "You grab the bundle of cash while noticing the computer doesn't seem to be in good shape."
// Answer Text :
"P2837220902" "Get out of there before any Hero stops by."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DocQuantum 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2571346689" "Although you're probably working with Shock Treatment and BOTH of you walked right into our sting operation, what would the chances be that you just HAPPEN to be in the nearby area?  And just HAPPEN to have found our decoy safe? And just HAPPEN to be here when Shock showed up?<br><br>So what do you say? What are the chances that would all happen at the same time, eh?"
// Answer Text :
"P1425270336" "There's a 17 percent chance it'll happen 23 percent of the time."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P991950120" "What? A 17 percent chance that -  Wait... That doesn't even make sense!"
// Answer Text :
"P980859006" "It does if you divide by infinity."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1100187856" "Divide by infinity, you say? Hmmm... That could take a little while.<br><br>Okay, I'll trust you for now.  But... If that money just HAPPENS to be gone, {HeroName}...<br><br>Well, the percentage chance of you spending time in the Zig is in the triple digits."
// Answer Text :
"P2711043912" "You mean thiiiiiis money?... *Do a magic trick!*"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P2135988054" "<color orange>You do the 'Coin-Behind-the-Ear' trick on Doc Quantum.  However, instead of a coin, it's the bundle of cash we're about to 'redistribute'. </color><br><br>But... But how did it... I don't...<BR><BR>HOW'S THAT EVEN POSSIBLE?"
// Answer Text :
"P3717488511" "I told you - divide by infinity!  In the meantime, I'm gonna get a bite to eat."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P158471689" "You can't believe your luck.  Stardusk kept her personal information in the file of her blog?  How stupid can you get?<br><br>Sure enough, inside the file was the combination to a safe in a warehouse tucked neatly away in Paragon City.<br><br>All of your new friends here are beginning to trust you; you don't want to ruin a good thing by getting caught jumping on an easy opportunity to make some fast cash.  Howeverrrrrr... this IS a villain's ill-gotten gains we're talking about.  AND she's illegally hiding it in Paragon City.<br><br>That's not really stealing, right?"
// AcceptString :
"P4032888236" "No.  It's not stealing.  Not at all."
// SendOffString :
"P4053155128" "Looking at the address of the warehouse, you remember being there at some point in the past.  If you remember correctly, that place is likely guarded by hired security.  BUUUUUT!  But they're being paid with dirty money, so it's not like you're really hurting the good guys if you have to crack a few of their skulls... right?"
// ActiveTaskString :
"P1719335588" "Nope.  Not at all.  Now go get that cash!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1034014051" "If you plan on stealing all that easy cash - no, not steal... 'redistribute'... - then you're going to need to get to that warehouse before Stardusk finds out she's a moron and gave all her info away.  Get to that safe in the warehouse!"
// TaskTitle :
"P3439463389" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Backdoor Entry</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1450955378" "So far so good.  Looks like Stardusk hasn't found out yet that she's about to lose a big chunk of her cash.  Get to that safe before your hero buddies know you're missing."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3572140303" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Backdoor Entry</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>So it turns out the blog, password, safe - all of it - was actually a sting operation being carried out to round up stupid criminals.  However, with some quick thinking you were able to bluff your way out of any blame - at the cost of handing over the money!<br><br>Quantum didn't realize the real magic trick was that the cash DIDN'T disappear."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P856364347" ""
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3571567476" "Now we die..."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2470932519" "Trick Doc Quantum into letting you go!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3143181850" "Stardusk's Electronic Safe"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1329285424" "This safe has been disguised to look like an old broken computer, but you know differently."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1738482053" "Nevermind"

