// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_RogToHero_SL4-5_Task_07 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - CrybabyHero 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3235491978" "Why, {HeroName}?  Why are you always picking on me?  What in this godforsaken earth would make you pick me to be your punching bag?"
// Answer Text :
"P3351187860" "WHO.  ARE.  YOU.  KID?"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P3173488809" "I'm Private Punishment, son of General Justice! You don't remember me, do you? I told my dad you wouldn't, and he said that I needed to 'be a man' and face you down anyways.<br><br>I guess it doesn't matter who I am in the end, does it?  You'll still beat me up even if you can't remember my name."
// Answer Text :
"P450074089" "Look... I have a hard time with faces, okay?"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P4174789586" ""Not with mine, you don't.  You always seem to have an easy time punching it, pummeling it, poking it, and other 'p' words, too.<br><br>Well, it doesn't matter anymore.  I give up.  I was going to trick you and use the statis field generater I found here when I would play with my do- action figures. But that would turn me into the same thing you are.<br><br>So I decided I'd do what my dad said and call you out. But I was too weak to defeat  you.<br><br>And I made the choice that if I couldn't beat you, I would just hand myself over to the Council and let them do with me what they wanted to.  So that's what I'm going to do."
// Answer Text :
"P1119950137" "Don't be stupid, kid!  They'll-"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P2311689454" "See!?  Now I'm stupid, too?  Fine!<br><br>Then if {HeroName} says I'm stupid, then I guess I'm stupid, too!<br><br>Either way, I'm giving up.  Take that *stupid* stasis field and go do *stupid* evil things with it.  I don't care anymore.  I'm just going to go be *stupid* in front of the *stupid* Council."
// Answer Text :
"P3278481713" "Get back here, kid!  Only a moron would -"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - CrybabyHeroAgain 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2766880905" "I think I learned a little about myself today.  I called you out, but you met my challenge. But instead of fighting, you were there to help build up my confidence.<br><br>Then I went off to get myself killed, but you came to rescue me so I didn't make a permanent decision.<br><br>After facing down all those guys, and even stopping that really scary metal guy from killing me, you're listening to me talk about what I learned today.  Do you know what I ultimately realized?"
// Answer Text :
"P1531584105" "That people can change and better themselves?"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1356542677" "No.<br><br>I learned that you're a better person than me.<br><br>And that makes me the MOST PATHETIC PERSON IN THE WORRRRLLLDDDD!"
// Answer Text :
"P1355976811" "No! Kid, that's not what- aw... Who cares?  I GIVE UP!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2017996493" "Are you serious?  This kid thinks you're his archnemesis or something?  You don't even know who this kid is, let alone want to act that part for him!  This kid has some seriously misguided views on things, judging by his silly costume.  Even if, for some INSANE reason you actually faced him, well, he better not wear that stupid, stupid costume - I mean, C'MON... wings on his helmet and a smiling skull on his shirt?  Sheesh.<br><br>  Normally you wouldn't care but, you know... there's something about this kid that reminds you of yourself when you were his age.  Except far less pathetic.  And nowhere as dumb.<br><br>And a MUCH better costume."
// AcceptString :
"P2841522198" "Talk some sense into the stupid kid."
// SendOffString :
"P636407260" "If you don't talk some sense into that kid soon, he'll wind up getting himself killed.  And not in a cool way, either.  More like falling off a car or choking to death on a piece of popcorn or by rabid kittens.<br><br>You agree to his challenge under the condition he doesn't wear that dumb costume.  According to his response back to you, it looks like where he's chosen to meet you is - A COUNCIL FORTRESS?!?!<br><br>What is that kid thinking!?! You better get over there and knock some sense into him before the Council does."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P111019804" "Go save that stupid kid!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P855078456" "If you don't get to that kid first, the Council will.  Then how are you going to live with that on your conscience?<br><br>Okay, well maybe it might upset your breakfast...<br><br>Okay, who are we kidding? It won't bug you in the least.<br><br>But hey... got anything else better to do?  Didn't think so.  So go save him."
// TaskTitle :
"P219126929" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Private Punishment</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3264065209" "Okay, this should be the place.  You'd better find that little snot before he gets his face beat in by the Council."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P301705068" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Private Punishment</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You managed to save the stupid kid's life several times, but in the end it seems that trying to help him turned out far worse than if you had not cared at all.<br><br>However, you did get a chance to reflect on the similarities between him and when you were his age.  Now you realize you were OUT OF YOUR MIND when you thought he reminded you of when you were younger.<br><br>And you ALWAYS had a better costume."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1600956904" "Talk to the stupid kid"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P544049937" "Survive the Council trap"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2338097853" "Let the kid shower you in his gratitude"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1803687427" "Private Punishment"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P659442170" "A hero who can't seem to cut it, even though he keeps trying as hard as he can."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3297440439" "I knew he wouldn't show.  {HeroName} was just mocking me.  Again."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2696914555" "Well, well, well.<em t=3>So we meet once again, {HeroName}. And now it's time for our dance of conflict to end."
// Script Variable BOSS_1STBLOOD_DIALOG :
"P2178976262" "This is for all the times you sent me to the hospital!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1852014356" "And this is for the time when you stole my helmet.<em t=3>And my shirt.<em t=3>And my woobie."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3140099750" "And this is for my turtle Beauford, may she rest in peace.<em t=3>POPPA'S COMING FOR YOU, BEAUFORD!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P264033086" "OKAY!  FINE!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DEAD_DIALOG :
"P3589091583" "...you win."
// Script Variable BOSS_KILLEDHERO_DIALOG :
"P2610653668" "Huh?  I... I beat {HeroName}?<em t=3>I DID IT! I BEAT {HeroName}!<em t=3> LOOOO-ZUUUURRRR!"

